        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Alamere Falls</h2>
        <p>The most popular longer trail on the Point Reyes Peninsula is the 7.9 mile (12.7 km) round-trip Coast Trail, which leads to <strong>Alamere Falls</strong>. This stunning waterfall drops onto the beach and flows into the ocean.
        <!-- Read More Read Less Tab -->
        <div class="hidden-content">
            <p>Just behind the giant beach waterfall are several smaller waterfalls, which lead to the main falls. The trail to reach Alamere Falls winds up coastal cliffs before passing through the forest with multiple small lakes along the way, until concluding at the falls and the beach.</p>
        </div>
